1. Grincon1 hosted at c-base, Berlin (https://github.com/mimblewimble/grin-pm#grincon1)

2. Website redesigned and moved to grin.mw

3. Ivan Bogatyy "breaks" MW's privacy model (https://medium.com/dragonfly-research/breaking-mimblewimble-privacy-model-84bcd67bfe52). Response by Grin team (https://medium.com/grin-mimblewimble/factual-inaccuracies-of-breaking-mimblewimbles-privacy-model-8063371839b9)

4. Moved meetings from gitter to keybase

5. http transaction deprecated. Now Tor/slatepacks (https://docs.grin.mw/about-grin/transactions/). Exchanges are not happy about this. (https://forum.grin.mw/t/potential-deprecation-of-http-s-transaction-building/7297/3)

6. Grin's 3.0 hard fork fixed a CVE that left MWC and other Grin forks vulnerable to a hack (https://www.mwc.mw/mimble-wimble-coin-articles/hotbit-update)

7. MAJOR UI improvement, security audit, and website update for Grin++ (https://forum.grin.mw/t/grin-updates/7314)

8. Surprise, surprise, Bitgrin, a scammy fork of Grin, is outed as a scam (https://medium.com/@pharozen/bitgrin-xbg-just-scammed-you-f856d44a19c9)

9. Grin community admin's funds stolen from Kucoin. :pepecry:  (https://reddit.com/r/kucoin/comments/ih5res/kucoin_account_hacked/)

10. Asic AMA with iPollo. First hint at the iPollo G1-Mini. (https://github.com/mimblewimble/grin-pm/blob/master/notes/20200811-meeting-governance.md#6-grin--asics-ama-with-thomas-and-kevin-from-vidtoo--canaan--bitrise-capital)

11. Grin Hub Telegram community moved to GrinPrivacy (https://twitter.com/grin_privacy/status/1325616441719054336)

12. 51% attacked through NiceHash (1: https://github.com/Grinnode-live/grinnode.live/blob/master/documentation/attacks/2020_11_reorg-51-percent.md). Community funded instance of the Grin NiceHash Defender bot created (https://grindefender.online/)

13. Early, exclusive sale for the G1-Mini to grin forum users. (https://forum.grin.mw/t/ended-sales-in-forum-for-ipollo-g1-mini-miner-with-exclusive-discount-and-20-donation-promise/8089)

14. Grin bug challenge hosted by grinnode.live in preparation for the final hard fork (https://grinnode.live/challenge/1)

15. Grin forked to the last of the scheduled hard fork on Jan 16, 2021 after 2 long years.

16. Yeastplume's memo for a split community fund (https://gist.github.com/yeastplume/5d1913c7dc40c40f409ffcfe8fa9b094)

17. Devastating inflation bug caught early by Grin++. $250k bounty awarded to David Burkett (https://forum.grin.mw/t/ann-bug-bounty-awarded-to-david-burkett-grin/8672)

18. Voting for community candidates started. Still ongoing (https://forum.grin.mw/t/call-for-grin-community-candidates-for-additional-fund-granting-control/8521/4)

19. Grin meme contest (https://forum.grin.mw/t/announcing-grin-it-to-win-it-best-meme-bounty/8701)

20. F2pool shuts down their grin mining pool, and now goblinpool (run by Niffler wallet dev, xiaojay) has 70% of graphrate


From Aug 2019?
There's a lot and I probably missed some important ones.
